The paper discusses the use of random feature maps to reduce the dimensionality of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of hashing pipelines, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper's focus on reducing computational intensity and preserving accuracy suggests that it may also fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of Kac's random walk matrices suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
